From the Jesuit Relations 12:191-2.  
> All these barbarians have the law of wild asses - they are born, live, and die in liberty without restraint; they do not know what it is meant by bridle or bit.  With them, to conquer one's passions is a great joke, while to to five free rein to the senses is a lofty philosophy.

Questions: 
> Is this a helpful definition of sorts for freedom?
> How might this help inform us about Jesuit thinking about freedom---both as a concept and the evaluation of that concept?
